    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="nar.01338.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
           <ab>April 21, 1870</ab>
           <ab>Hon. Reverdy Johnson</ab>
           <ab>Baltimore, Md.</ab>
           <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>Agreeably to your request I send you an Opinion of the Attorney General, given April 27, 1869, relating to the compensation of Collectors, naval officers, and surveyors of customs. I have obtained the consent of the Secretary of the Treasury that this Opinion may be sent you. </ab><note type="authorial" place="left">trans. copy of opinion</note>
           <ab>I have the honor to be,</ab>
           <ab>Very respectfully,</ab>
           <ab>W. A. Field.</ab>
           <ab>Assistant Attorney General.</ab>
        </body>
    </text>
